section.def:
client contract (客戶合約) means any contract or arrangement between an intermediary and its
            client, which contains terms on which the intermediary is to provide services the
            provision of which constitutes a regulated activity;

subsection.def:
aggregate margin loans (保證金貸款總額), in relation to an intermediary, means the
                sum of margin loans owed to the intermediary by its margin clients as at the close
                of business on the relevant business day;

margin client (保證金客戶) has the meaning assigned to it by section 2(1) of the
                Securities and Futures (Financial Resources) Rules (Cap. 571
                    sub. leg. N);

section.def:
intermediary (中介人)
            means a licensed corporation, or an authorized financial institution, that is licensed
            or registered for Type 13 regulated activity;
